      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOW HIGH (6) goes very well at this journey having never missed the frame including four wins and two placings. Scored by 2.5 lengths last time (25.12) in a Grade 5 over 440m at this track. Rates a leading player. PAW ZEVA (1) has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by 4 lengths at Bulli in a handy 19.16 beating Spencer Fury. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. One of the key runners again. RED ROCK RAZZLE (4) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 520m at Wentworth Park, taking a Grade 4/5 in a powerful 29.59. Should be in this for a long way. WRITTEN IN GOLD (2) deserves plenty of thought at his first run at this circuit.",
